assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. engages in the production and sale of industrial rubber components in Japan. It manufactures and sells industrial materials, including pneumatic controllers, anti-vibration mounts, and peripherals; printing materials; electrical and electronic equipment; rescue and life-saving equipment; and carbon shafts for golf clubs. The company also offers gas/water residential equipment to control and regulate the gas and water; rubber packings, sealing materials, admixtures, etc. for connection and branching of communication cables; fire prevention sheets; rubber blankets for various offset printing, such as books, magazines, newspapers, packages, metal deco, drink cans, plastic cups, and others; and audio cone material. In addition, it provides check valve; automotive parts, such as engines, brakes, and ventilation; industrial equipment, including duct quarter vent rubber/butterfly, and BF and AB cylinder; calendared rubber, such as anti-vibration system and pressure regulator; ultra-low hardness material and anti-vibration rubber products; paper roll airbags; conductive cushion, anti-static, and electromagnetic shield for electric circuit; textile/material for clothing; static removal sheet, cushion sheet, and pad for semicon and LCD production lines; and silicone blanket for printed electronics. Further, the company offers emergency magnesium air batteries; blade protective sheets for wind turbine; various tapes for electric, cable connection, and repair; various molded products; cold shrink tubings; conservators; LIM products; dialyzers; proportional valves; latex products; disaster tents, life jackets, air tents, and life rafts; graphite shaft for golf clubs; caravan shoes for climbing/trekking/hiking; and climbing/bouldering shoes. The company was formerly known as Fujikura Rubber Ltd. and changed its name to FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. in April 2019. FUJIKURA COMPOSITES Inc. was founded in 1901 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
